      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Neil was appointed as Change Director General in April 2019 in addition to retaining accountability to Parliament as Senior Responsible Owner (<abbr title="Senior Responsible Owner">SRO</abbr>) for Universal Credit.</p>

<p>Neil’s career started in a local benefits office administering claims for Income Support. His subsequent roles have included:</p>

<ul>
  <li>working in policy</li>
  <li>Principal Private Secretary to the Secretary of State</li>
  <li>several executive roles within Jobcentre Plus and its predecessors</li>
  <li>Director General for the Universal Credit Programme since October 2014</li>
</ul>

</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_5322">
            <h1 id="change-director-general-and-senior-responsible-owner-universal-credit">Change Director General and Senior Responsible Owner Universal Credit</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>In his role as Change Director General Neil is accountable to the <abbr title="Department for Work and Pensions">DWP</abbr> Permanent Secretary for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>leadership of <abbr title="Department for Work and Pensions">DWP</abbr>’s Major Change Portfolio</li>
  <li>delivering the overall objectives of the Major Change Portfolio</li>
  <li>the agreed delegated Major Change Portfolio budget</li>
  <li>leading Senior Responsible Owners (<abbr title="Senior Responsible Owners">SROs</abbr>) and Programme Directors in line with the corporate structure</li>
</ul>

<p>As <abbr title="Senior Responsible Owner">SRO</abbr> for Universal Credit he is accountable to Parliament for implementing the government’s main welfare reform programme. This includes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>owning and communicating the vision of the programme</li>
  <li>ensuring the implementation of Universal Credit is completed safely and securely</li>
  <li>providing clear leadership to the programme team</li>
</ul>

</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions">Department for Work and Pensions</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>      </div>

